<br>
I have to agree with Rexfelix that I found the original post to be a little bit offensive.  When I think of safe space, I think of an area where people are free to be whatever they are .. not some exclusive club where one or both sides looks at the other with a condescending &quot;how quaint&quot; attitude.  I'd like to see a culture built on this server where people are free to RP to whatever extent they wish, without people judging them, either because they aren't roleplaying, or roleplaying &quot;good&quot; enough, or because they are roleplaying.  In other words, a culture of *inclusion* and not *exclusion*.  I know that us vs them is the psychologically easiest way to build a community, but I've never been for taking the easy route <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
